# Python
**/.venv/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Secrets — never commit
**/.env
**/credentials.json
**/token.json

# Private config, secrets, runtime state
**/instance/
**/config.json
**/forclaude.txt
**/.scan_state.json

# Generated data (spreadsheets contain real contact info)
**/data/*.xlsx
**/data/*.xlsx#
~$*.xlsx

# Sample / business documents (proposals, forms, notices, exports) — never commit.
# These are confidential deliverables; keep them out of the (public) repo.
*.zip
*.pdf
*.doc
*.docx
*.xlsx

# Reference materials / firm data folders
**/assets/refs/
**/data/

# Scratch
**/scratch_*

# === docs/ framework — private working notes (BEGIN, managed by documentation skill) ===
# These stay local and are NEVER pushed to GitHub, in every project, public or
# private, so the private set is identical everywhere. Templates stay tracked so
# the structure is still visible. Session handoffs are also mirrored to the
# local Claude memory dir, so ignoring them here does not lose them.
docs/sessions/*
!docs/sessions/_TEMPLATE.md
!docs/sessions/README.md
docs/audits/*
!docs/audits/_TEMPLATE.md
!docs/audits/README.md
# === docs/ framework — private working notes (END) ===
